criteria.inclusion_criteria:
1. High risk AML patients 60-100 days after allo-HSCT and without aGVHD;
2. Aged < 60, KPS score > 60,expected survival > 3 months;
3. No serious organ dysfunction;
4. Informed consent.

criteria.exclusion_criteria:
1. Have serious organ dysfunction;
2. Combined with other cancer need treatment;
3. Presence of clinical signs of brain dysfunction or severe mental illness can not comply with the study protocol;
4. Can not guarantee the completion of the treatment plan and the necessary follow-up observation.
